description: Geelong forward Jeremy Cameron left the field clutching at his broken ribs after a collision with Essendon defender Jayden Laverde. Cameron did not return to the field for his side's 66-point victory over Essendon at the MCG. The former Giant has since been taken to hospital, struggling to breathe and stand up straight. Cameron had booted two goals for the Gunners in the first term.

one.description: Jeremy Cameron taken to hospital during Geelong's 66-point win over Essendon. The 28-year-old collided with Essendon defender Jayden Laverde during the first quarter at the MCG on Saturday. Cameron was struggling to breathe in the Cats' rooms, indicating a possible internal injury to his rib or lungs. Sam De Koning entered the AFL's 12-day concussion protocols after appearing to hit Esava Ratugolea.
